WEBVTT

00:04.414 --> 00:07.219
_

00:07.392 --> 00:12.587
<font color="#fff00">Synced
by Bakugan</font>

00:12.847 --> 00:14.181
[THUNDER]

00:14.223 --> 00:15.891
MAN: Of all the ties that bind,

00:15.933 --> 00:18.936
none is more profound than family.

00:21.355 --> 00:25.317
In 1836, Sarah Hart welcomed

00:25.359 --> 00:28.529
her recently orphaned
12-year-old niece Mary

00:28.571 --> 00:32.073
into her New Haven, Connecticut, home.

00:32.116 --> 00:34.410
Mary's parents had been lost at sea.

00:35.995 --> 00:37.747
Sara and Mary

00:37.788 --> 00:40.207
found solace in each other's company.

00:41.792 --> 00:43.294
As the years passed,

00:43.335 --> 00:45.796
they became inseparable.

00:45.838 --> 00:50.551
It was as if they were
of one mind, one heart.

00:51.802 --> 00:52.928
One morning,

00:52.970 --> 00:54.430
as the two women worked,

00:54.472 --> 00:56.474
Mary collapsed.

00:56.515 --> 00:58.559
The cause wasn't clear.

00:58.601 --> 01:00.394
[PANTING]

01:00.436 --> 01:04.482
At first Sara thought her
niece had simply fainted,

01:04.522 --> 01:06.275
but no.

01:06.317 --> 01:08.819
Sara held Mary in her arms

01:08.861 --> 01:10.571
as she took her last breath.

01:13.991 --> 01:16.118
She was buried the next day.

01:20.289 --> 01:23.501
That night, Sara had a nightmare.

01:29.757 --> 01:31.634
[THUMPING, SHOUTING]

01:31.675 --> 01:32.968
FEMALE VOICE: Let me out of here!

01:33.010 --> 01:34.804
Help! [SCREAMING]

01:34.845 --> 01:36.055
Help!

01:36.096 --> 01:37.473
[CRYING]

01:37.515 --> 01:39.475
Help!

01:39.517 --> 01:40.643
[SCREAMING]

01:40.684 --> 01:42.061
She was convinced

01:42.102 --> 01:43.979
this had to be more than a dream.

01:44.021 --> 01:47.191
Could Mary still be alive?

01:47.233 --> 01:51.153
She begged the church
officials to unearth Mary.

01:51.195 --> 01:54.740
It was a somber task that
quickly turned to horror

01:54.782 --> 01:58.202
when they laid eyes on
Mary's lifeless body...

01:58.244 --> 02:00.663
fingernails torn and bloody,

02:00.704 --> 02:03.749
the lining of the coffin torn to shreds.

02:06.335 --> 02:09.170
Her face a horrid death mask.

02:11.924 --> 02:13.884
This really happened to Mary Hart

02:13.926 --> 02:18.097
on October 16, 1872.

02:18.138 --> 02:22.643
Waking up inside a small
box 6 feet in the earth

02:22.685 --> 02:24.770
is what true fright looks like to me...

02:24.812 --> 02:26.939
buried but not dead,

02:26.981 --> 02:30.901
or, even worse, buried but undead.

02:32.903 --> 02:36.407
I'm Aaron Mahnke, and this is Lore.

02:38.000 --> 02:44.074
